Anh - Anh
cantoris
[kan'tɔ:rɪs]
■ noun the section of a church choir conventionally placed on the north side and taking the second or lower part in antiphonal singing. Compare with decani.
Origin
C17: from L., lit. 'of the cantor' (see cantor).
